    {
      "id": "e31f42237132382e8cdbd7c9b41029f7f92bfdde",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 123,
        "name": "Erich Focht",
        "email": "efocht@gmail.com",
        "username": "efocht",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-12-03 10:18:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThe patch changes the old behavior and contradicts the comment \"We don't know the failover node name, so just use the first nid as the uuid\".\n\nThe original way was: if a failnode has multiple NIDs, select the first one as the failnodeuuid, add all its NIDs to it (as possible connections).\n\nThe behavior in this patch is to set each NID of a failnode as separate failnodeuuid, and only add itself as connection.\n\nIf each node should have just one failnodeuuid (and that's what the variable name suggests), then this must be set in the inner while() if unset, and reset right after the inner while() block.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
